  "owner": "frank (Hawaiian Data Collector)",
  "tracks_issue": "#16",
  "purpose": "Pinned Stage-2 verse-aligned Bible source registry. Defines the (Hawaiian, English) edition pair the verse-id adapter targets, plus URL templates for raw fetch. URLs and edition years here are TENTATIVE pins pending Linus rights review (see data-sources/stage2-parallel-fetch-plan.json verification_status='pending_rights_review' for bible-haw-baibala-pinned-edition).",
  "boundaries": [
    "Adapter must run dry-run-by-default. Live --execute requires (a) Linus' written edition pin merged into this file and (b) ToS snapshot captured under data/raw/<source_id>/<YYYYMMDD>/tos_snapshot.html.",
    "Hawaiian text MUST be NFC-normalized with ʻokina canonicalized to U+02BB before any sha256 / pair-id is computed.",
    "Verse-id alignment is deterministic across editions ONLY when both sides share canonical book/chapter/verse keys. Versification differences (e.g., Psalms in Hebrew vs LXX) must be reconciled or the row dropped.",
    "Bible token share must stay <= 30% of Stage-2 parallel-train tokens; 0% of dev/test (see docs/data-pipeline.md §'Stage 2 source tiers' Tier A). The candidate emitter sets split='train' uniformly; allocation is Linus' responsibility downstream."
  ],
